verses.rendering:
I have sunk into deep mud where there is no foothold;
I have come into the depths of water,
and the flood sweeps over me.

I am exhausted from calling out;
my throat is raw.
My eyes fail from waiting for my God.

Do not let the floodwater sweep me away;
do not let the deep swallow me;
do not let the pit close its mouth over me.

Insult has broken my heart, and I am sick.
I looked for sympathy, but there was none;
for comforters, but I found none.

For God will save Zion
and rebuild the cities of Judah;
they will settle there and possess it.
